EthnoHealer Disclaimer

Last Updated: February 15, 2026

The information provided by EthnoHealer (“we”, “our”, “us”) on the EthnoHealer application (“App”) is for educational, informational, and cultural purposes only.

By using the App, you acknowledge and agree to this Disclaimer.

1. Not Medical Advice

EthnoHealer does not provide medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment.

All content available in the App — including:

Traditional remedies

Herbal information

Cultural healing practices

Community discussions

Wellness tips

is intended for general knowledge and educational purposes only.

Nothing in the App should be considered a substitute for:

Professional medical advice

Diagnosis from a qualified healthcare provider

Treatment from licensed medical practitioners

Emergency medical services

Always seek the advice of a qualified physician or healthcare professional before making any health-related decision.

Never ignore professional medical advice because of something you read on EthnoHealer.

2. No Doctor–Patient Relationship

Use of this App does not create a doctor–patient or healthcare provider–patient relationship between you and EthnoHealer or any users of the platform.

3. Traditional & Cultural Knowledge Notice

EthnoHealer shares traditional, indigenous, and cultural healing knowledge that may:

Not be scientifically tested

Vary across regions and cultures

Be based on historical or community practices

Such information should be approached responsibly and used at your own discretion.

